race.comment: SHE'S THE RUMOUR (10) resumes and has also switched stables. Found a place at Balaklava in her only fresh run and went close here before the spell. Gets Holder and will be naturally improved. TAHNEE TERRITORY (11) resumes for a new yard and would be a chance if she's on song. Has trialled well and Crowther sticks aboard. No surprise to see her finishing hard. CLASSY CLARET (1) resumes and will come into his own over longer trips. He has his share of ability and may be more forward this time around. This isn't strong, and keep a close eye on the betting moves. TIDDY WIDDY (12) found one much too good here last time, but it was an improved effort following a freshen. She is yet to recapture her strong early form, but will be fitter and is in light with the 3kg claim. Has a wide gate to manage, but keep onside.
